result.execSummary:
The defendant Monique Monetta Banks was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Monique Monetta Banks is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Monique Monetta Banks was found guilty of Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called at 2:54 PM.  Defendant Monique Monetta Banks in court.  The State of Wisconsin appeared by Jenna Gill.  Ms. Banks informs the Court that she would like to proceed today without an attorney.  Court advises Ms. Banks of all the possible disadvantages and consequences of proceeding today without an attorney.  Defendant has received copy of criminal complaint in matter.  Court questions Defendant regarding understanding and comprehending the English language and what she is being charged with.  Defendant is waiving conflict of interest regarding Attorney Guy Taylor representing her.  Court will accept Attorney Guy Taylor representing Defendant today.  Attorney Taylor has conversation with Defendant regarding her rights.  Court questions Defendant regarding plea questionnaire and waiver of rights.  Defendant enters plea of Guilty due to no contest on count 1.  Court is satisfied that Defendant enters her plea knowingly, voluntarily, intelligently, and freely.   Defendant makes statement to the Court.  Court will adopt recommendations of resolution.

Case called at 2:56 PM.  Defendant Monique Monetta Banks in court.  Special Appearance by Attorney Guy Taylor.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Matter continued.  Arraignment scheduled for January 24, 2017 at 02:00 pm.

Case called at 1:48 PM.  Defendant Monique Monetta Banks in court, in custody.   Attorney Guy Taylor appeared by phone.  Katherine M. Findley appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DE does have a copy of the criminal complaint in the matter.  Court has reviewed the criminal complaint and has found probable cause.  State is requesting $200.00 cash bail.  Court sets signature bond at $1,000.00.
